::Pyramid Principle Three Rules::According to the lecture, which of the following is one of the three rules of the Pyramid Principle?{
=Ideas above must summarize those below #This is Rule 1 of the Pyramid Principle — ideas at any level must summarize the ideas grouped below them. This allows readers to stop at any level.
~All arguments must use the same data source #The Pyramid Principle doesn't require using the same data source. Rule 2 states grouped ideas must be logically the same kind, not from the same source.
